her is to bust out the ole whirl series and keep em spinnin indefinately while the pet munches away at their life.  Also when doing the bard remember to wait like 10 seconds after any successful mez's for their song to stop before doing anything else. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1E1E1E><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uerylflynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eryl Flynn</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Real Slim Shady</span><br>  Posts: 351<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/12/00 12:42:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.dimensional.com/~malekith/ef1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just being a paladin or a bard </span><hr size=1> But enchanters and bards have an ace up their sleeves.  Seems if you charm a player and do /pet get lost the target can't cast til they log or zone. <p>Eryl Flynn Level 49 Wood Elf Bard on Prexus
