<br>
As a necro instead of dotting myself I just use Lich. It causes enuff damage to keep mezz off and returns mana after ToT. Screaming Terror seemed to get resisted too often against Bloodrose so I assume that would be any chanter with their MR.<br>
<br>
If you could dark and fear them before you dot them along with the pet then you are golden. It was tuff to keep a dot on her cause she keep them dispelled. So my conclusion came to this.<br>
<br>
Let the chanter deal with your pet while you root them (I must of chased Bloodrose around for 15 minutes) and just Deflux them to death. Deflux is a 3 second cast time 330hp lifetap that is very rarely resisted. Keep em rooted or in darkness if you can and drain them to death.<br>
<br>
I conceded to Bloodrose, she had me anyways but by lifetapping her to death I prolly would have won. An enchanters nukes are very slow casting and are resisted alot.<br>
<br>
